    <link>https://forums.gauntlet-rpg.com/t/recommendations-pretty-games-awesome-presentation/1057</link>
    <description>Once in awhile, you crack open a book and are just completely, utterly blown away. Maybe it&#39;s the artwork, distinctive and evocative. Maybe it&#39;s the layout, clear and informative. Maybe it&#39;s the packaging, the extra tools like dice or game pieces. Sometimes it&#39;s all of these.

**Quick List of Recommendations**
These links point outward to the books, scroll down for individual posts-- often with pictures!

* [Dialect](https://thornygames.com/pages/dialect)
* [Troika: Numinous Edition](https://www.melsonia.com/troika-17-p.asp)
* [Nobilis: Great White Book Edition](https://rpggeek.com/rpgitem/44919/nobilis-2nd-edition)
* [Bluebeard&#39;s Bride](https://www.magpiegames.com/bluebeards-bride/)
* [Godsend](https://ufopress.co.uk/2018/06/11/godsend-in-depth/)
* [Blue Rose: The AGE RPG of Romantic Fantasy](https://greenroninstore.com/products/blue-rose-the-age-rpg-of-romantic-fantasy)
* [Shadows of Esteren](https://www.drivethrurpg.com/product/109112/Shadows-of-Esteren--Book-0-Prologue)
* [Itras By](https://itrasby.com/about/)
* [1001 Nights: Narrativa’s Italian edition](http://www.narrattiva.it/it/shop/fantasy/mille-e-una-notte/)
* [Good Society](https://storybrewersroleplaying.com/good-society/)
* [Fate to go: German Steelcase Edition](https://www.sphaerenmeisters-spiele.de/epages/15455106.sf/en_US/?ObjectPath=/Shops/15455106/Products/VWF2G01)
* [Night Witches: Korean Edition](https://www.tumblbug.com/nightwitches)
* [Lovecraftesque: Narrativa Edition](http://www.narrattiva.it/it/shop/fantasy/lovecraftesque/)
* [Spire](http://rowanrookanddecard.com/product/spire-rpg/)
* [Tales from the Loop](https://www.modiphius.net/products/tales-from-the-loop-rpg-rulebook)
* [Blades in the Dark](https://www.evilhat.com/home/blades-in-the-dark/)
* [Misspent Youth](http://misspentyouthgame.com/)
* [Ryuutama](http://kotohi.com/ryuutama/)
* [Fate of the Norns](https://www.fateofthenorns.com/store/)
* [Mothership](http://www.tuesdayknightgames.com/mothership)
* [The Sprawl: German Edition](https://shop.uhrwerk-verlag.de/rollenspiele-uhrwerk-verlag/909-der-sprawl-grundregelwerk-hc-9783958671195.html)


(If you include a link to more details in your recommendation, I&#39;ll use that. Otherwise, for books still in print, I&#39;ve defaulted to the publisher website. Everything else, I&#39;ll try to link to RPGgeek or similar. Hope that&#39;s okay!)

**What do you like?** 
I really want to hear your recommendations about books to appreciate, not just as games, but as objects. Post a reply below and I&#39;ll try and edit it into a list here.</description>
    
