          <blockquote>
              <p>I think the new <a href="https://www.melsonia.com/troika-17-p.asp" rel="nofollow noopener">Troika Numinous Edition</a> really hits the mark in layout terms for those classic english printed works. The font and art choices really do a lot of work but also layout. It uses lots of columns like the printed works it is referencing and only uses justification where it doesn’t cause too much space. The pages also have plenty of white space and keep one idea to its own page in a smart way. For different sections the white background color subtly shifts which can give it that old paper feel but also makes for useful reference.<br>
